### UMS CALCULATION SYSTEM

**OFFICIAL WMA12 GRADE BOUNDARIES (reference — verify at qualifications.pearson.com):**

| Series | Max | a | b | c | d | e | u |
|--------|-----|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Jan 2022 | 75 | 57 | 49 | 41 | 34 | 27 | 0 |
| Oct 2022 | 75 | 57 | 50 | 43 | 36 | 29 | 0 |
| Jan 2023 | 75 | 55 | 47 | 39 | 32 | 25 | 0 |
| Jun 2023 | 75 | 60 | 53 | 46 | 39 | 33 | 0 |
| Jan 2024 | 75 | 58 | 51 | 44 | 37 | 31 | 0 |
| Oct 2024 | 75 | 56 | 49 | 42 | 35 | 29 | 0 |
| Jan 2025 | 75 | 57 | 50 | 43 | 36 | 30 | 0 |

> ⚠️ Always verify actual boundaries at qualifications.pearson.com. WMA12 boundaries shift between sessions.

**UMS SCALE:** a=80–100 / b=70–79 / c=60–69 / d=50–59 / e=40–49 / u=0–39

**UMS INTERPOLATION FORMULA:**
```
UMS = lower_UMS + [(raw - lower_raw) / (upper_raw - lower_raw)] × (upper_UMS - lower_UMS)
```

**CONFIDENCE FLAG RULES:**
- `CONFIRMED` = raw mark clearly within a band, not within 2 marks of a grade boundary
- `BORDERLINE ±1` = raw mark within 2 marks of a grade boundary

**ERROR TYPE CLASSIFICATION:**
- **METHOD error**: Wrong technique entirely — loses M and all dependent A marks
- **ARITHMETIC slip**: Correct method, minor numerical error — loses A mark only, M preserved
- **MISSING WORKING**: Correct answer, no method shown — loses M and dependent A
- **KNOWLEDGE gap**: Student does not know the required technique or formula

